.TH "MESSAGEPORT.MESSAGEERROR_EVENT" "3JS" "September 6, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
MessagePort.messageerror_event \- MessagePort: messageerror event
.SH SYNOPSIS
\f[B]Note:\f[R] This feature is available in Web Workers.
.PP
The \f[B]\f[CB]messageerror\f[B]\f[R] event is fired on a
\f[CR]MessagePort\f[R] object when it receives a message that can\(cqt
be deserialized.
.PP
This event is not cancellable and does not bubble.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqmessageerror\(dq, (event) => { })

onmessageerror = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A \f[CR]MessageEvent\f[R].
Inherits from \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EVENT PROPERTIES
\f[I]This interface also inherits properties from its parent,
\f[CI]Event\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]MessageEvent.data\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
The data sent by the message emitter.
.TP
\f[B]MessageEvent.origin\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A string representing the origin of the message emitter.
.TP
\f[B]MessageEvent.lastEventId\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A string representing a unique ID for the event.
.TP
\f[B]MessageEvent.source\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
A \f[CR]MessageEventSource\f[R] (which can be a WindowProxy,
\f[CR]MessagePort\f[R], or \f[CR]ServiceWorker\f[R] object) representing
the message emitter.
.TP
\f[B]MessageEvent.ports\f[R] \f[I](read\-only)\f[R]
An array containing all \f[CR]MessagePort\f[R] objects sent with the
message, in order.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Attempting to share memory
A common cause of \f[CR]messageerror\f[R] events is attempting to send a
\f[CR]SharedArrayBuffer\f[R] object, or a buffer view backed by one,
across agent clusters.
For example, a window is not in the same agent cluster as a shared
worker it created, so suppose the page runs the following code:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] worker = \f[B]new\f[R] SharedWorker(\(dqworker.js\(dq);
worker.port.start();
worker.port.addEventListener(\(dqmessage\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  worker.port.postMessage(\f[B]new\f[R] SharedArrayBuffer(1024));
});
.EE
.PP
And \f[CR]worker.js\f[R] contains the following code:
.IP
.EX
self.addEventListener(\(dqconnect\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(\(dqHello\(dq);
  \f[B]const\f[R] port = event.ports[0];
  port.start();
  port.postMessage(\(dqPort connected\(dq);
  port.addEventListener(\(dqmessageerror\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    console.log(\(dqMessage error\(dq);
  });
});
.EE
.PP
Then the shared worker will receive a \f[CR]messageerror\f[R] event when
it tries to deserialize the message sent from the window.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] You can use browser devtools to debug your SharedWorker,
by entering a URL in your browser address bar to access the devtools
workers inspector; for example, in Chrome, the URL
\f[CR]chrome://inspect/#workers\f[R], and in Firefox, the URL
\f[CR]about:debugging#workers\f[R].
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.IP \(bu 2
Related events: \f[CR]message\f[R].
